00:04:49.160 --> 00:04:51.410 align:middle line:84%
For me, the most
interesting thing

00:04:51.410 --> 00:04:55.280 align:middle line:84%
that I learned about physics was
quantum physics at UC Berkeley.

00:04:55.280 --> 00:04:58.670 align:middle line:84%
I loved my classes in
that subject matter.

00:04:58.670 --> 00:05:01.460 align:middle line:84%
And after my
Kundalini awakening,

00:05:01.460 --> 00:05:05.930 align:middle line:84%
I came to realize that a
lot of the answer to what

00:05:05.930 --> 00:05:08.510 align:middle line:84%
is the nature of
reality seems to be

00:05:08.510 --> 00:05:12.590 align:middle line:84%
held in the mysteries of quantum
physics, which, although we can

00:05:12.590 --> 00:05:15.040 align:middle line:84%
work out the mathematics
and we can solve equations

00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:19.580 align:middle line:84%
and we can even build atomic
bombs and nuclear power plants,

00:05:19.580 --> 00:05:24.980 align:middle line:84%
we don't exactly think the
way quantum physics shows us

00:05:24.980 --> 00:05:27.080 align:middle line:90%
that the world really operates.

00:05:27.080 --> 00:05:31.340 align:middle line:84%
And what's so wonderful and
mysterious about the quantum

00:05:31.340 --> 00:05:33.920 align:middle line:84%
physics and quantum
mechanics is that when

00:05:33.920 --> 00:05:37.490 align:middle line:84%
we look to see, what are these
building blocks of matter,

00:05:37.490 --> 00:05:41.150 align:middle line:84%
we find that at the very
center of the very smallest

00:05:41.150 --> 00:05:44.120 align:middle line:84%
inseparable, indivisible
particle, which

00:05:44.120 --> 00:05:46.730 align:middle line:84%
would be like an
electron, if you can't

00:05:46.730 --> 00:05:48.230 align:middle line:84%
get any smaller
than that, then that

00:05:48.230 --> 00:05:50.840 align:middle line:90%
qualifies as a quantum particle.

00:05:50.840 --> 00:05:52.940 align:middle line:84%
Those little
electrons can actually

00:05:52.940 --> 00:05:57.390 align:middle line:84%
be observed to be in one place,
and then it's like they vanish.

00:05:57.390 --> 00:06:01.350 align:middle line:84%
They can change in energy level
and show up instantly somewhere

00:06:01.350 --> 00:06:02.150 align:middle line:90%
else.

00:06:02.150 --> 00:06:03.620 align:middle line:90%
And they do other things also.

00:06:03.620 --> 00:06:07.370 align:middle line:84%
They can be connected with
one another, entangled.

00:06:07.370 --> 00:06:10.730 align:middle line:84%
And when one is affected
and its spin is up

00:06:10.730 --> 00:06:14.990 align:middle line:84%
and the other one's spin is
down, if you observe one,

00:06:14.990 --> 00:06:16.730 align:middle line:84%
as soon as you make
an observation on one

00:06:16.730 --> 00:06:18.440 align:middle line:84%
that's entangled with
another, they both

00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:19.910 align:middle line:90%
flip at the same time.

00:06:19.910 --> 00:06:21.890 align:middle line:84%
These entanglements
are now being

00:06:21.890 --> 00:06:24.560 align:middle line:84%
tested in laboratory
conditions around the world

00:06:24.560 --> 00:06:27.200 align:middle line:84%
as people are building
quantum computers.

00:06:27.200 --> 00:06:30.020 align:middle line:84%
There's been a race,
like a gold rush

00:06:30.020 --> 00:06:33.170 align:middle line:84%
to see how fast we can
find this information

00:06:33.170 --> 00:06:34.700 align:middle line:90%
and these new technologies.

00:06:34.700 --> 00:06:37.310 align:middle line:84%
So diamonds and
large things that you

00:06:37.310 --> 00:06:39.770 align:middle line:84%
can observe in your hands
are being entangled.

00:06:39.770 --> 00:06:41.450 align:middle line:84%
They're showing
entanglements that

00:06:41.450 --> 00:06:45.390 align:middle line:84%
are holding together at
greater and greater distances.

00:06:45.390 --> 00:06:48.530 align:middle line:84%
So we can tell obviously
throughout the universe

00:06:48.530 --> 00:06:51.980 align:middle line:84%
there can be an entanglement
with one particle right here

00:06:51.980 --> 00:06:55.550 align:middle line:84%
and another particle in an
entirely different galaxy,

00:06:55.550 --> 00:06:56.840 align:middle line:90%
great distances away.

00:06:56.840 --> 00:07:00.740 align:middle line:84%
So there seems to be no
limitation on the distance.

00:07:00.740 --> 00:07:03.350 align:middle line:84%
When we look at space
and time, then we

00:07:03.350 --> 00:07:06.410 align:middle line:84%
start recognizing that humans
have a unique experience

00:07:06.410 --> 00:07:07.790 align:middle line:90%
with space and time.

00:07:07.790 --> 00:07:11.180 align:middle line:84%
And what we think is
true for everything

00:07:11.180 --> 00:07:14.090 align:middle line:84%
may not be true for
everything, but may more

00:07:14.090 --> 00:07:17.240 align:middle line:84%
be a facet of our
humanity and the way

00:07:17.240 --> 00:07:19.655 align:middle line:84%
that we are set up
to observe reality.

00:07:19.655 --> 00:07:26.260 align:middle line:90%


00:07:26.260 --> 00:07:28.620 align:middle line:84%
The Mandela effect
is a term that

00:07:28.620 --> 00:07:33.210 align:middle line:84%
was coined in the year 2010
by a blogger, Fiona Broome.

00:07:33.210 --> 00:07:36.060 align:middle line:84%
And she and a bunch
of people noticed

00:07:36.060 --> 00:07:39.240 align:middle line:84%
that they remembered
that the gentleman named

00:07:39.240 --> 00:07:44.010 align:middle line:84%
Nelson Mandela from South
Africa had died before 2010.

00:07:44.010 --> 00:07:47.700 align:middle line:84%
They were all surprised and glad
that he was alive, but really

00:07:47.700 --> 00:07:50.700 align:middle line:84%
surprised because they
remembered clearly

00:07:50.700 --> 00:07:52.950 align:middle line:90%
that he had previously died.

00:07:52.950 --> 00:07:56.880 align:middle line:84%
So this was the first
time that the idea

00:07:56.880 --> 00:07:59.040 align:middle line:84%
of a whole bunch of people
remembering something

00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:02.520 align:middle line:90%
differently really caught hold.

00:08:02.520 --> 00:08:07.260 align:middle line:10%
And it became very popular
on Reddit, that website,

00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:09.600 align:middle line:10%
as well as the
Mandela effect website

00:08:09.600 --> 00:08:11.700 align:middle line:10%
that Fiona Broome started.

00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:14.040 align:middle line:84%
And actually, this
is a phenomenon

00:08:14.040 --> 00:08:16.290 align:middle line:84%
that I've been tracking
since the 1990s.

00:08:16.290 --> 00:08:18.600 align:middle line:84%
It's what I would
call reality shift.

00:08:18.600 --> 00:08:22.980 align:middle line:84%
And that was a term that was
coined by PMH Atwater when

00:08:22.980 --> 00:08:25.750 align:middle line:84%
she wrote an earlier book that
I didn't know about at the time.

00:08:25.750 --> 00:08:27.720 align:middle line:84%
So I found that the
word reality shift

00:08:27.720 --> 00:08:30.300 align:middle line:84%
seemed to explain there
are a bunch of people

00:08:30.300 --> 00:08:33.429 align:middle line:84%
that notice someone died,
and now they're alive again.

00:08:33.429 --> 00:08:35.760 align:middle line:84%
I noticed Larry Hagman,
and I wrote about him

00:08:35.760 --> 00:08:37.360 align:middle line:90%
in my book "Reality Shifts."

00:08:37.360 --> 00:08:39.870 align:middle line:84%
He's an actor from
the TV show "Dallas."

00:08:39.870 --> 00:08:43.140 align:middle line:84%
So I described that lots of
people noticed he had died,

00:08:43.140 --> 00:08:45.090 align:middle line:90%
and then he was alive again.

00:08:45.090 --> 00:08:47.220 align:middle line:84%
It's a phenomenon
that's very interesting,

00:08:47.220 --> 00:08:52.260 align:middle line:84%
because the closer you are to
Larry Hagman or Nelson Mandela,

00:08:52.260 --> 00:08:54.630 align:middle line:84%
the less likely
you are to notice

00:08:54.630 --> 00:08:57.120 align:middle line:84%
that particular
individual had died

00:08:57.120 --> 00:08:58.560 align:middle line:84%
and then they'd
come alive again.

00:08:58.560 --> 00:09:01.050 align:middle line:84%
It's more likely to
happen when it's someone

00:09:01.050 --> 00:09:02.700 align:middle line:90%
that you don't see very often.

00:09:02.700 --> 00:09:04.740 align:middle line:84%
You don't really
think about them much.

00:09:04.740 --> 00:09:07.290 align:middle line:84%
They're on the periphery
of your awareness.

00:09:07.290 --> 00:09:08.940 align:middle line:90%
They're not the focal point.

00:09:08.940 --> 00:09:10.080 align:middle line:90%
They're off to the side.

00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:12.480 align:middle line:84%
So you know about them, and
then when you hear about it,

00:09:12.480 --> 00:09:13.110 align:middle line:90%
it's like, wow.

00:09:13.110 --> 00:09:13.910 align:middle line:90%
That's big.

00:09:13.910 --> 00:09:16.560 align:middle line:84%
So that was the beginning
of this Mandela effect.

00:09:16.560 --> 00:09:21.340 align:middle line:84%
It has now exploded in terms
of lots of other examples.

00:09:21.340 --> 00:09:23.730 align:middle line:10%
Books, movies, you
name it, products.

00:09:23.730 --> 00:09:25.840 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] All kinds of things.

00:09:25.840 --> 00:09:27.630 align:middle line:84%
So when it comes
to things like we

00:09:27.630 --> 00:09:30.600 align:middle line:84%
notice products changing,
that can be confusing,

00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:33.090 align:middle line:84%
because of course, first
you want to make sure,

00:09:33.090 --> 00:09:35.260 align:middle line:84%
was it really some
kind of a change?

00:09:35.260 --> 00:09:36.870 align:middle line:90%
Did the company make a change?

00:09:36.870 --> 00:09:39.120 align:middle line:84%
Once you eliminate
that possibility,

00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:42.540 align:middle line:84%
then the only thing
left is that when

00:09:42.540 --> 00:09:45.240 align:middle line:84%
you're the one that noticed
the change, unless you

00:09:45.240 --> 00:09:47.880 align:middle line:84%
think you're going crazy
or getting forgetful.

00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:49.570 align:middle line:90%
Usually, this is not the case.

00:09:49.570 --> 00:09:51.270 align:middle line:84%
Usually, people that
notice these things

00:09:51.270 --> 00:09:52.380 align:middle line:90%
are very observant.

00:09:52.380 --> 00:09:54.480 align:middle line:10%
They're getting an
opportunity to experience

00:09:54.480 --> 00:09:56.190 align:middle line:10%
these alternate histories.

00:09:56.190 --> 00:09:57.810 align:middle line:10%
And what's happening
is one group

00:09:57.810 --> 00:10:00.540 align:middle line:10%
of people would notice it
like with Nelson Mandela.

00:10:00.540 --> 00:10:03.900 align:middle line:84%
The ones who don't live in South
Africa like myself and others,

00:10:03.900 --> 00:10:06.720 align:middle line:84%
they remember he died
when he was incarcerated.

00:10:06.720 --> 00:10:08.040 align:middle line:90%
He was still in jail.

00:10:08.040 --> 00:10:10.390 align:middle line:90%
And it seemed such a tragedy.

00:10:10.390 --> 00:10:11.730 align:middle line:90%
It seemed very sad.

00:10:11.730 --> 00:10:14.940 align:middle line:84%
And then there was
a big hullabaloo.

00:10:14.940 --> 00:10:18.060 align:middle line:84%
There were lots of things
going on with his widow

00:10:18.060 --> 00:10:21.090 align:middle line:84%
and the government and
trying to work things out

00:10:21.090 --> 00:10:22.020 align:middle line:90%
with the estate.

00:10:22.020 --> 00:10:24.540 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, it's not
confabulation, which

00:10:24.540 --> 00:10:27.120 align:middle line:84%
is what some people say
the Mandela effect is.

00:10:27.120 --> 00:10:29.250 align:middle line:84%
They say, well, you're
just making this up.

00:10:29.250 --> 00:10:32.230 align:middle line:84%
But why would so many
people make that up?

00:10:32.230 --> 00:10:34.780 align:middle line:84%
As far as how it
works, I don't know.

00:10:34.780 --> 00:10:36.490 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm not going
to just say, like,

00:10:36.490 --> 00:10:38.980 align:middle line:84%
oh, I've got a theory
that explains everything.

00:10:38.980 --> 00:10:41.650 align:middle line:84%
Instead, I am more
like a biologist,

00:10:41.650 --> 00:10:44.720 align:middle line:84%
back when biologists
would travel the world

00:10:44.720 --> 00:10:47.380 align:middle line:84%
to see if they could categorize
what kind of birds and animals

00:10:47.380 --> 00:10:48.490 align:middle line:90%
they're observing.

00:10:48.490 --> 00:10:52.210 align:middle line:10%
Just like when Charles Darwin
is on the "Beagle," that ship,

00:10:52.210 --> 00:10:53.960 align:middle line:10%
and he's traveling
across the world,

00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:57.350 align:middle line:10%
that's what I've been doing with
these reality shift examples.

00:10:57.350 --> 00:10:59.170 align:middle line:84%
So I'm still
gathering information.

00:10:59.170 --> 00:11:02.110 align:middle line:84%
But it's possible that
what we're looking at

00:11:02.110 --> 00:11:05.740 align:middle line:84%
is something that's similar
to a holographic multiverse.

00:11:05.740 --> 00:11:08.020 align:middle line:84%
So there's a
holographic component

00:11:08.020 --> 00:11:10.060 align:middle line:84%
where everything is
connected and it's one,

00:11:10.060 --> 00:11:12.350 align:middle line:90%
like the pages in a book.

00:11:12.350 --> 00:11:18.310 align:middle line:84%
But each page might signify
another parallel reality, which

00:11:18.310 --> 00:11:19.690 align:middle line:90%
could be side by side by side.

00:11:19.690 --> 00:11:23.290 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes you can jump
from one page to another.

00:11:23.290 --> 00:11:25.870 align:middle line:84%
Where everybody else is,
that gets to the question

00:11:25.870 --> 00:11:27.160 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:11:27.160 --> 00:11:30.760 align:middle line:84%
And how can each
of us hold ideas

00:11:30.760 --> 00:11:33.470 align:middle line:84%
that might be from
some other reality?

00:11:33.470 --> 00:11:36.550 align:middle line:84%
Then we need to start taking a
look at what some people might

00:11:36.550 --> 00:11:39.670 align:middle line:84%
call are these
anomalous experiences.

00:11:39.670 --> 00:11:42.887 align:middle line:84%
But to me, I think they're
pretty common experiences.

00:11:42.887 --> 00:11:44.470 align:middle line:84%
And I think we're
seeing more evidence

00:11:44.470 --> 00:11:49.150 align:middle line:84%
of this sort of quantum
behavior in all of biology,

00:11:49.150 --> 00:11:51.280 align:middle line:90%
in all of life.

00:11:51.280 --> 00:11:54.310 align:middle line:10%
There are an infinity
of possibilities

00:11:54.310 --> 00:11:57.370 align:middle line:10%
that at every moment we make a
choice, we're looking at that

00:11:57.370 --> 00:11:58.640 align:middle line:10%
and feeling that.

00:11:58.640 --> 00:12:02.350 align:middle line:84%
And so people who've had
near-death experiences

00:12:02.350 --> 00:12:05.920 align:middle line:84%
or are lucid dreamers or have
had a Kundalini experience,

00:12:05.920 --> 00:12:08.860 align:middle line:84%
they're much more keenly
aware of this process,

00:12:08.860 --> 00:12:11.950 align:middle line:84%
and they can feel
when they're in it.

00:12:11.950 --> 00:12:13.900 align:middle line:84%
And it's pretty
remarkable, because you

00:12:13.900 --> 00:12:16.900 align:middle line:84%
can tell that there's a reality
that's always been there.

00:12:16.900 --> 00:12:19.150 align:middle line:84%
It's not so much that you're
creating it or calling it

00:12:19.150 --> 00:12:20.140 align:middle line:90%
to you.

00:12:20.140 --> 00:12:23.020 align:middle line:84%
It's more that you
are recognizing

00:12:23.020 --> 00:12:26.140 align:middle line:84%
that the truth of who
you are is consciousness.

00:12:26.140 --> 00:12:29.620 align:middle line:84%
And as consciousness, you're
capable of making that jump

00:12:29.620 --> 00:12:31.480 align:middle line:90%
into any reality.

00:12:31.480 --> 00:12:34.180 align:middle line:84%
Which sounds
incredible, but people

00:12:34.180 --> 00:12:36.100 align:middle line:84%
who have come back
from being dead

00:12:36.100 --> 00:12:38.570 align:middle line:84%
will sometimes report that's
exactly what they did.

00:12:38.570 --> 00:12:42.730 align:middle line:84%
And that's how they were able
to become fully healed when they

00:12:42.730 --> 00:12:44.530 align:middle line:90%
were extremely sick before.

00:12:44.530 --> 00:12:49.970 align:middle line:90%


00:12:49.970 --> 00:12:53.840 align:middle line:84%
Actually, most of us do
experience these quantum jumps.

00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:56.210 align:middle line:84%
And we don't think much
of it when it happens.

00:12:56.210 --> 00:12:59.270 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we are just
happy that it happens.

00:12:59.270 --> 00:13:02.540 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking right
now of the example where

00:13:02.540 --> 00:13:05.810 align:middle line:84%
if you need to wake up and
you have trouble waking up

00:13:05.810 --> 00:13:07.550 align:middle line:84%
and you will yourself
to get out of bed

00:13:07.550 --> 00:13:09.680 align:middle line:84%
on a cold morning,
that willpower,

00:13:09.680 --> 00:13:11.810 align:middle line:90%
that moment is an example of it.

00:13:11.810 --> 00:13:14.090 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't sound very
impressive, I know.

00:13:14.090 --> 00:13:16.970 align:middle line:84%
And then one that's a little bit
more impressive but still not

00:13:16.970 --> 00:13:18.540 align:middle line:90%
that impressive-- so it's easy.

00:13:18.540 --> 00:13:20.460 align:middle line:84%
These are a little baby
step quantum jumps.

00:13:20.460 --> 00:13:23.330 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHS] Another good
one that's easy to do is

00:13:23.330 --> 00:13:26.010 align:middle line:10%
if you're starting to catch a
cold and you can tell yourself,

00:13:26.010 --> 00:13:27.780 align:middle line:10%
I can't get sick today--

00:13:27.780 --> 00:13:30.470 align:middle line:10%
and I think we've all had that
experience where it's like, no.

00:13:30.470 --> 00:13:31.580 align:middle line:90%
This is not happening.

00:13:31.580 --> 00:13:33.380 align:middle line:90%
I have to stay well today.

00:13:33.380 --> 00:13:36.660 align:middle line:84%
And then you notice, after
I thought that, I felt fine.

00:13:36.660 --> 00:13:38.413 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people have
that experience.

00:13:38.413 --> 00:13:39.830 align:middle line:84%
And then one that's
scientifically

00:13:39.830 --> 00:13:41.840 align:middle line:84%
proven in the
laboratories right now

00:13:41.840 --> 00:13:43.940 align:middle line:84%
is where you know for
sure that you did not

00:13:43.940 --> 00:13:45.290 align:middle line:90%
get a good night's sleep.

00:13:45.290 --> 00:13:48.560 align:middle line:84%
Maybe there was a
neighbor fighting or lots

00:13:48.560 --> 00:13:50.087 align:middle line:90%
of noise, traffic accidents.

00:13:50.087 --> 00:13:51.920 align:middle line:84%
Something going on that
was so noisy there's

00:13:51.920 --> 00:13:54.110 align:middle line:84%
no way you got a
good night's sleep.

00:13:54.110 --> 00:13:56.240 align:middle line:84%
It was the worst
night's sleep ever.

00:13:56.240 --> 00:13:57.770 align:middle line:84%
In the morning,
all you need to do

00:13:57.770 --> 00:13:59.780 align:middle line:84%
is keep telling
yourself over and over

00:13:59.780 --> 00:14:02.220 align:middle line:84%
and over again until
you start believing it,

00:14:02.220 --> 00:14:04.250 align:middle line:84%
I had a wonderful
night's sleep last night.

00:14:04.250 --> 00:14:05.990 align:middle line:84%
And you just keep
repeating that, just

00:14:05.990 --> 00:14:08.690 align:middle line:84%
starting to believe
it, convince yourself.

00:14:08.690 --> 00:14:10.310 align:middle line:84%
Then what's
scientifically proven

00:14:10.310 --> 00:14:14.300 align:middle line:84%
is that you will behave on
all sorts of cognitive tests,

00:14:14.300 --> 00:14:17.510 align:middle line:84%
physical tests just the same as
if you'd had that good night's

00:14:17.510 --> 00:14:19.410 align:middle line:90%
sleep, and you'll feel better.

00:14:19.410 --> 00:14:21.070 align:middle line:84%
So these are things
that are easy.

00:14:21.070 --> 00:14:22.580 align:middle line:90%
On the other extreme--

00:14:22.580 --> 00:14:24.980 align:middle line:84%
because I like to look
at the entire bandwidth,

00:14:24.980 --> 00:14:26.870 align:middle line:84%
the whole breadth
and depth of it.

00:14:26.870 --> 00:14:29.820 align:middle line:84%
At the other extreme that's
going to start sounding crazy,

00:14:29.820 --> 00:14:33.110 align:middle line:84%
I've heard from so many people
that have instantaneously

00:14:33.110 --> 00:14:35.240 align:middle line:84%
been teleported to
safety when they've

00:14:35.240 --> 00:14:38.082 align:middle line:84%
been in an accident, when
their car is about to crash.

00:14:38.082 --> 00:14:40.040 align:middle line:84%
They don't know what
happened, but somehow they

00:14:40.040 --> 00:14:42.200 align:middle line:90%
got thrown clear of the vehicle.

00:14:42.200 --> 00:14:44.030 align:middle line:84%
It's as if they went
right through it.

00:14:44.030 --> 00:14:48.080 align:middle line:84%
Or maybe the oncoming
vehicle never hit their car,

00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:51.290 align:middle line:84%
but now is on the other side,
and there never was an impact,

00:14:51.290 --> 00:14:52.490 align:middle line:90%
never was a collision.

00:14:52.490 --> 00:14:54.530 align:middle line:84%
This is basically
quantum tunneling,

00:14:54.530 --> 00:14:58.640 align:middle line:84%
and it's happening with a
Mack truck and a car, vehicles

00:14:58.640 --> 00:15:01.310 align:middle line:84%
that weigh thousands and
thousands of kilograms.

00:15:01.310 --> 00:15:02.570 align:middle line:90%
It is extremely heavy.

00:15:02.570 --> 00:15:04.320 align:middle line:84%
And so there's no
way to explain that.

00:15:04.320 --> 00:15:06.030 align:middle line:90%
And these things happen a lot.

00:15:06.030 --> 00:15:08.030 align:middle line:84%
There are lots and lots
of examples of that,

00:15:08.030 --> 00:15:11.330 align:middle line:84%
as well as instantaneous
healing of everything

00:15:11.330 --> 00:15:15.140 align:middle line:84%
from broken bones, which are
not supposed to heal instantly,

00:15:15.140 --> 00:15:17.630 align:middle line:90%
to cancer going away.

00:15:17.630 --> 00:15:19.940 align:middle line:84%
When we look at what
the healers are doing,

00:15:19.940 --> 00:15:23.115 align:middle line:84%
they're able to enter a
dream with their client

00:15:23.115 --> 00:15:23.915 align:middle line:90%
or with a person.

00:15:23.915 --> 00:15:27.200 align:middle line:10%
And when I say dream, that's
recognizing that all of reality

00:15:27.200 --> 00:15:28.460 align:middle line:10%
is like a dream.

00:15:28.460 --> 00:15:32.030 align:middle line:10%
And this is what you hear
if you study the Upanishads

00:15:32.030 --> 00:15:33.500 align:middle line:10%
and some Indian writing.

00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:36.430 align:middle line:84%
They'll tell you,
reality is a dream.

00:15:36.430 --> 00:15:39.620 align:middle line:84%
So when you enter the dream with
someone, then you share that.

00:15:39.620 --> 00:15:44.170 align:middle line:84%
And you can enter the dream and
help the person find that dream

00:15:44.170 --> 00:15:46.120 align:middle line:90%
reality where they are healthy.

00:15:46.120 --> 00:15:49.570 align:middle line:84%
And that is exactly what
healers are able to do,

00:15:49.570 --> 00:15:51.103 align:middle line:90%
is to go there with someone.

00:15:51.103 --> 00:15:53.020 align:middle line:84%
And then when they come
back on that journey--

00:15:53.020 --> 00:15:55.930 align:middle line:84%
and it might be with drumming
or it might be with chanting.

00:15:55.930 --> 00:15:58.510 align:middle line:84%
These are what indigenous
peoples the world over

00:15:58.510 --> 00:15:59.680 align:middle line:90%
have used as a--

00:15:59.680 --> 00:16:02.020 align:middle line:84%
these are ancient
technologies that

00:16:02.020 --> 00:16:06.560 align:middle line:84%
are very effective at
implementing quantum jumps.

00:16:06.560 --> 00:16:08.468 align:middle line:84%
I think the reason
most people don't

00:16:08.468 --> 00:16:10.010 align:middle line:84%
think that these
things are happening

00:16:10.010 --> 00:16:13.400 align:middle line:84%
or don't think they're observing
them is primarily because they

00:16:13.400 --> 00:16:14.930 align:middle line:90%
don't believe it's possible.

00:16:14.930 --> 00:16:16.280 align:middle line:90%
That's the first thing.

00:16:16.280 --> 00:16:19.910 align:middle line:84%
And secondly, there's an
open-mindedness issue,

00:16:19.910 --> 00:16:22.430 align:middle line:84%
because once you believe,
well, it's possible,

00:16:22.430 --> 00:16:25.520 align:middle line:84%
then you need to even be
even more open-minded so

00:16:25.520 --> 00:16:27.740 align:middle line:84%
that those kind of
experiences could happen.

00:16:27.740 --> 00:16:29.657 align:middle line:84%
You wouldn't think it
would make a difference,

00:16:29.657 --> 00:16:32.510 align:middle line:84%
but it really does, because
our brains and our minds

00:16:32.510 --> 00:16:36.260 align:middle line:84%
are set up to observe what we
train ourselves to look for.

00:16:36.260 --> 00:16:39.770 align:middle line:84%
And if we're not looking for
these kinds of quantum jumps,

00:16:39.770 --> 00:16:42.470 align:middle line:84%
reality shifts, Mandela
effects, then we

00:16:42.470 --> 00:16:44.000 align:middle line:90%
don't really notice them.

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:46.970 align:middle line:84%
Or we assume, first of all,
that we've made a mistake.

00:16:46.970 --> 00:16:50.330 align:middle line:84%
We think, well, maybe
I'm misremembering that.

00:16:50.330 --> 00:16:53.420 align:middle line:84%
Maybe there's some reason that
when I talk about my childhood

00:16:53.420 --> 00:16:55.460 align:middle line:84%
with my family,
they tell a story

00:16:55.460 --> 00:16:59.060 align:middle line:84%
that I know didn't happen, and
they seem so convinced it did.

00:16:59.060 --> 00:17:02.270 align:middle line:84%
We just dismiss those signs
and those pieces of evidence

00:17:02.270 --> 00:17:03.890 align:middle line:84%
that would suggest
that we're all

00:17:03.890 --> 00:17:05.900 align:middle line:84%
experiencing
alternate histories,

00:17:05.900 --> 00:17:08.730 align:middle line:90%
and that it's quite normal.

00:17:08.730 --> 00:17:11.630 align:middle line:84%
So when people assume that
we're just going through

00:17:11.630 --> 00:17:13.430 align:middle line:84%
like watching a
movie on the screen,

00:17:13.430 --> 00:17:17.540 align:middle line:84%
and we want the illusion that
that movie is flowing evenly,

00:17:17.540 --> 00:17:19.700 align:middle line:84%
and it's just as
good as real life.

00:17:19.700 --> 00:17:22.829 align:middle line:84%
Actually, we're watching
frames in a movie flashing.

00:17:22.829 --> 00:17:25.520 align:middle line:84%
So it's a lot more
like stair steps,

00:17:25.520 --> 00:17:28.590 align:middle line:84%
like taking step by
step by step by step.

00:17:28.590 --> 00:17:31.050 align:middle line:84%
I believe that's also
what nature is doing.

00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:34.580 align:middle line:84%
And so we'll be able to start
seeing more evidence of it

00:17:34.580 --> 00:17:38.030 align:middle line:84%
by recognizing that this
can and does happen.

00:17:38.030 --> 00:17:40.220 align:middle line:84%
And we're seeing
things that I would

00:17:40.220 --> 00:17:44.600 align:middle line:84%
expect to find such as
when scientists have a bias

00:17:44.600 --> 00:17:47.150 align:middle line:84%
to begin with to expect
a certain result,

00:17:47.150 --> 00:17:49.490 align:middle line:84%
that's the result
they tend to get.

00:17:49.490 --> 00:17:51.500 align:middle line:84%
Some of our
Nobel-winning scientists

00:17:51.500 --> 00:17:53.360 align:middle line:90%
are noticing that too.

00:17:53.360 --> 00:17:58.400 align:middle line:84%
They tend to think that there's
some sort of observer bias,

00:17:58.400 --> 00:18:02.120 align:middle line:84%
but I'm considering it's a
deeper problem, that actually

00:18:02.120 --> 00:18:05.730 align:middle line:84%
we can change results just by
expecting something different.

00:18:05.730 --> 00:18:07.280 align:middle line:84%
And then we can do
that on any scale.

00:18:07.280 --> 00:18:12.680 align:middle line:90%


00:18:12.680 --> 00:18:14.870 align:middle line:10%
I like people who are
skeptical about this,

00:18:14.870 --> 00:18:18.080 align:middle line:10%
because I think that's
good to be skeptical,

00:18:18.080 --> 00:18:19.160 align:middle line:10%
to be a good skeptic.

00:18:19.160 --> 00:18:21.650 align:middle line:84%
And open-minded but
questioning, like, OK.

00:18:21.650 --> 00:18:23.040 align:middle line:90%
This doesn't make any sense.

00:18:23.040 --> 00:18:24.350 align:middle line:90%
This is not what I learned.

00:18:24.350 --> 00:18:26.760 align:middle line:84%
So how can this
possibly be true?

00:18:26.760 --> 00:18:30.950 align:middle line:84%
And for them, I would suggest
looking at placebo studies.

00:18:30.950 --> 00:18:33.920 align:middle line:84%
Placebo is a word that
means, I shall please.

00:18:33.920 --> 00:18:37.970 align:middle line:10%
And in World War II, there
were doctors in England

00:18:37.970 --> 00:18:39.800 align:middle line:10%
that were running
out of medication,

00:18:39.800 --> 00:18:42.380 align:middle line:10%
and so they would basically
give the soldiers who

00:18:42.380 --> 00:18:45.830 align:middle line:10%
were in a great deal of pain
an injection with just water

00:18:45.830 --> 00:18:47.250 align:middle line:10%
and some salt in it.

00:18:47.250 --> 00:18:49.520 align:middle line:90%
So it's just a saline solution.

00:18:49.520 --> 00:18:53.000 align:middle line:84%
And they would notice in
large numbers of people,

00:18:53.000 --> 00:18:54.200 align:middle line:90%
they would feel better.

00:18:54.200 --> 00:18:55.730 align:middle line:84%
The doctors wanted
to do something.

00:18:55.730 --> 00:18:58.160 align:middle line:84%
When they run out of
medicine on the front line,

00:18:58.160 --> 00:18:59.480 align:middle line:90%
that's a terrible feeling.

00:18:59.480 --> 00:19:01.310 align:middle line:84%
So this is why, if
you're wondering, well,

00:19:01.310 --> 00:19:04.580 align:middle line:84%
that sounds unethical, why would
doctors do that, that's why.

00:19:04.580 --> 00:19:07.160 align:middle line:84%
And right now in surveys
that are conducted

00:19:07.160 --> 00:19:11.000 align:middle line:84%
across all of the hospitals in
America, a majority of doctors

00:19:11.000 --> 00:19:14.420 align:middle line:84%
absolutely will prescribe
placebos for their patients,

00:19:14.420 --> 00:19:16.940 align:middle line:84%
because sometimes they
don't have anything

00:19:16.940 --> 00:19:18.470 align:middle line:84%
that they know for
sure will work,

00:19:18.470 --> 00:19:20.580 align:middle line:84%
and so they say,
well, take this.

00:19:20.580 --> 00:19:21.890 align:middle line:90%
We think it will help.

00:19:21.890 --> 00:19:25.130 align:middle line:84%
And the very fact that that's
